a kilowatt hour.

00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:53.160 align:middle line:90%
>>Amazing.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:56.130 align:middle line:84%
>>So a great incentive
that Germany has in place.

00:04:56.130 --> 00:05:01.130 align:middle line:84%
And so, photovoltaics is
going through miraculous turns

00:05:01.130 --> 00:05:04.740 align:middle line:84%
right now as we have finally
gone to war over oil.

00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:08.610 align:middle line:84%
So now the clock
is really ticking.

00:05:08.610 --> 00:05:14.260 align:middle line:84%
Wind energy, a very
ancient source of power.

00:05:14.260 --> 00:05:15.920 align:middle line:84%
There are-- I mean,
I could tell you

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:21.040 align:middle line:84%
stories about how,
for example, Holland,

00:05:21.040 --> 00:05:26.560 align:middle line:84%
which was a terribly
barren place in Europe

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:28.410 align:middle line:84%
with just the winds
of the North Sea

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:30.060 align:middle line:90%
blowing down on this country.

00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:33.490 align:middle line:84%
This little country developed
the first wind machines

00:05:33.490 --> 00:05:34.780 align:middle line:90%
in Europe.

00:05:34.780 --> 00:05:38.650 align:middle line:84%
And with it, began to have
the first windmills, which

00:05:38.650 --> 00:05:39.660 align:middle line:90%
in effect were used.

00:05:39.660 --> 00:05:44.380 align:middle line:84%
The giant band saws that
were cutting up the lumber.

00:05:44.380 --> 00:05:48.000 align:middle line:84%
Logs that were flowing down from
the Rhine River, from the Alps,

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:51.460 align:middle line:84%
were cut up into
more wind machines.

00:05:51.460 --> 00:05:54.080 align:middle line:84%
So the would machines were
reproducing themselves.

00:05:54.080 --> 00:05:57.270 align:middle line:84%
And also the making
of ships, which

00:05:57.270 --> 00:06:01.640 align:middle line:84%
were the Dutch, the East
India Company, all those ships

00:06:01.640 --> 00:06:03.990 align:middle line:90%
were made from wind machines.

00:06:03.990 --> 00:06:09.410 align:middle line:84%
And then, the Dutch millwrights
went to the bankers and said,

00:06:09.410 --> 00:06:11.170 align:middle line:90%
we have an incredible idea.

00:06:11.170 --> 00:06:12.474 align:middle line:90%
And they said, what is it?

00:06:12.474 --> 00:06:13.890 align:middle line:84%
They said, we know
how to increase

00:06:13.890 --> 00:06:15.930 align:middle line:84%
the size of the
country because we're

00:06:15.930 --> 00:06:18.180 align:middle line:84%
going to pump out all the
lakes and all the-- we're

00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:21.160 align:middle line:84%
going to pump out the
ocean of our country,

00:06:21.160 --> 00:06:24.480 align:middle line:84%
and increase the
size of our country.

00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:26.410 align:middle line:84%
So they received
immediate financing

00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:29.340 align:middle line:84%
from these very
successful groups,

00:06:29.340 --> 00:06:31.560 align:middle line:90%
and the bankers in Holland.

00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:33.340 align:middle line:84%
And then the final
experiment was

00:06:33.340 --> 00:06:38.370 align:middle line:84%
to put these prefabricated
wind machines made

00:06:38.370 --> 00:06:43.710 align:middle line:84%
from wind machines on ships
made from wind machines.

00:06:43.710 --> 00:06:46.470 align:middle line:84%
They then went to
the New World, set up

00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:48.600 align:middle line:84%
the wind machines
in Long Island,

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:52.430 align:middle line:84%
and built New Amsterdam, which
is today's New York City.

00:06:52.430 --> 00:06:53.170 align:middle line:90%
>>New York City.

00:06:53.170 --> 00:06:55.460 align:middle line:84%
>>So it's a very
ancient technology.

00:06:55.460 --> 00:07:02.780 align:middle line:84%
Now where it's come to
about the turn of the 19th

00:07:02.780 --> 00:07:07.290 align:middle line:84%
through the 20th
century, about 1900,

00:07:07.290 --> 00:07:09.800 align:middle line:84%
the first wind
machines out of Denmark

00:07:09.800 --> 00:07:11.630 align:middle line:90%
were producing electricity.

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:15.120 align:middle line:84%
And so over the
years, especially

00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:18.330 align:middle line:84%
with the-- what happened
was, the oil shocks

00:07:18.330 --> 00:07:23.440 align:middle line:84%
of the early '70s began
to create a great interest

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:26.000 align:middle line:84%
in producing electricity
from the wind.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:31.410 align:middle line:84%
So in California, we were
the first modern wind machine

00:07:31.410 --> 00:07:34.150 align:middle line:84%
company called
Aero Power Systems

00:07:34.150 --> 00:07:36.706 align:middle line:90%
about the same time, 1978.

00:07:36.706 --> 00:07:38.080 align:middle line:84%
And then all of
a sudden, we were

00:07:38.080 --> 00:07:41.290 align:middle line:84%
inundated by limited
partnerships wanting

00:07:41.290 --> 00:07:44.680 align:middle line:84%
to build wind farms
in Altamont Pass.

00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And so we were the
first at Altamont

00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:51.420 align:middle line:84%
Pass to do the site surveys
and to plan the first machines.

00:07:51.420 --> 00:07:58.680 align:middle line:84%
Where we are at now is wind
machines, wind turbines,

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:02.260 align:middle line:84%
are the most cost effective
of all renewable energy

00:08:02.260 --> 00:08:04.720 align:middle line:90%
machines and sources.

00:08:04.720 --> 00:08:10.810 align:middle line:84%
So we are now seeing tremendous
activity out of Germany,

00:08:10.810 --> 00:08:13.850 align:middle line:84%
which is the leader
right now, followed

00:08:13.850 --> 00:08:20.902 align:middle line:84%
by Spain, which is number
two, India, Greece.

00:08:20.902 --> 00:08:23.360 align:middle line:84%
Different parts of the world
where there is tremendous wind

00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:26.380 align:middle line:84%
resources are now
tapping into the wind.

00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:29.610 align:middle line:84%
So wind is the most
ready out of all of them.

00:08:29.610 --> 00:08:31.360 align:middle line:84%
>>Also, were they
