We are coming to the peak oil.

00:32:58.860 --> 00:33:02.184 align:middle line:84%
Some say it's already
happened, this is the peak.

00:33:02.184 --> 00:33:04.350 align:middle line:84%
From here on in, it's going
to get much, much harder

00:33:04.350 --> 00:33:07.810 align:middle line:90%
to find more fossil fuels.

00:33:07.810 --> 00:33:09.820 align:middle line:84%
These fossil fuels
are, in many cases,

00:33:09.820 --> 00:33:13.990 align:middle line:84%
in remote areas where very
unstable political situations,

00:33:13.990 --> 00:33:18.190 align:middle line:84%
thus our involvement in
the Mideast right now.

00:33:18.190 --> 00:33:22.270 align:middle line:84%
When at the same time, we have
the sun shining on our roofs

00:33:22.270 --> 00:33:22.910 align:middle line:90%
in the US.

00:33:22.910 --> 00:33:25.110 align:middle line:84%
We have the wind
blowing over our heads.

00:33:25.110 --> 00:33:28.770 align:middle line:84%
We have energy everywhere
available on the planet,

00:33:28.770 --> 00:33:29.390 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:33:29.390 --> 00:33:33.570 align:middle line:84%
So our focus has just
been on centralized power

00:33:33.570 --> 00:33:35.510 align:middle line:90%
and the liquid-fueled economy.

00:33:35.510 --> 00:33:39.280 align:middle line:84%
And what's ahead of
us now is to produce

00:33:39.280 --> 00:33:47.380 align:middle line:84%
sustainable green technologies
that can be locally produced,

00:33:47.380 --> 00:33:49.980 align:middle line:90%
that tap into local power.

00:33:49.980 --> 00:33:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's what's
in front of us.

00:33:52.010 --> 00:33:53.450 align:middle line:84%
>>So up until now,
in essence, we

00:33:53.450 --> 00:33:58.920 align:middle line:84%
have not been motivated
